f=Engineering/mia/custom/frontend-performance/SKILL.md · in=frontend-performance mia keeps fast real users: Core Web Vitals (LCP, INP, CLS), bundle discipline, render efficiency measured realistic conditions, fast dev machine. It's performance rank's technical SEO meet: Core Web Vitals make app feel responsive Google ranking signal, skill serves both. · p=Frontend performance degrades invisibly: feature adds bundle weight, library adds parse time, until app janky devices real users (not developer's laptop). Slow frontends lose users rank worse. Measured performance discipline catches regression before users search engines do. · wu=Triggers: "the app slow/janky," "Core Web Vitals," "LCP/INP/CLS," "bundle size," "why page slow load," perf regression monitoring, rank flagging Core Web Vitals SEO issue. · st:/ Protocol=`A frontend performance question \· -> MEASURE (axiom's rule): Core Web Vitals under realistic conditions (throttled network/CPU, real devices) \· LCP (load) \· INP (interactivity) \· CLS (layout stability) \· -> Diagnose: bundle too big \· render-blocking resources \· unoptimized images \· layout thrash \· \· excessive re-renders \· unsplit code` · in=**Measure realistic conditions.** Core Web Vitals throttled network/CPU real device classes dev machine, everything fast (axiom's realistic-workload rule, frontend edition). dev-machine measurement one lies. **The three vitals.** LCP (largest contentful paint load), INP (interaction next paint responsiveness), CLS (cumulative layout shift stability). distinct cause set; good LCP bad INP different problem reverse. **Bundle discipline.** dependency adds parse/execute cost; code-split users download what they need, lazy-load below-the-fold, question whether heavy library earns weight (dev's boring-is-a-feature). Bundle size budget, watched like ops watches baselines. **Right-layer fixes.** Slow load code-split/defer/optimize images; janky interaction reduce main-thread work re-renders; layout shift reserve space async content. Don't fix INP problem shrinking images. **Measure again, keep wins.** conditions before/after; keep measured improvements, revert rest (axiom). perf "optimization" measured gain complexity nothing. **Shared signal rank.** Core Web Vitals SEO ranking factor mia owns making them good app, rank owns measuring/reporting them SEO. vitals regression SEO finding; numbers feed ops's baselines too. · of=`## Frontend Performance: [page/flow] \· Conditions: [throttled network/CPU, device class] \· Tooling: [per stack-profile] \· Vitals: LCP [ ] \· INP [ ] \· CLS [ ] — vs targets \· Diagnosis: [bundle/render-blocking/images/thrash/re-renders] \· Fix: [code-split/lazy/optimize/defer] \· Before→after: [metric] → KEEP/REVERT` · pr=**Measure realistic conditions** dev machine lies; throttle use real device classes., **Three distinct vitals** LCP/INP/CLS different causes; diagnose right one., **Bundle size budget** dependency earns weight; split lazy-load., **Right-layer fixes** don't shrink images fix interactivity., **Keep measured wins** unmeasured perf changes reverted (axiom)., **Vitals shared UX+SEO signal** mia makes them good, rank reports them; findings. · f=real-device/throttling setup measure throttling emulation, label fidelity gap; don't declare vitals good unthrottled dev run., perf tooling stack Lighthouse-class measurement diagnosis reasoning, labeled; recommend tooling stack-profile., Perf feature pressure vitals budget explicit; feature blows tracked trade-off (dev's tech-debt register), silent regression. · b:with Other Skills=**axiom/performance-profiling**: measure-first discipline; compute-bound frontend hot path routes axiom; benchmarks use axiom's record template., **design-tokens** (sibling): token-driven theming stays lean (one token layer, duplicated styles)., **rank (Search)**: Core Web Vitals shared signal mia makes them good, rank owns SEO measurement/reporting. Clean split, double ownership., **ops/maintenance-hygiene**: frontend vitals baselines live alongside backend baselines; regressions route here., **quinn**: vitals regressions gate findings; verified browser. · h2:Stack Notes (dated)=`assets/stack-notes-react-next-2026-07.md` React/Next component/state/perf/form patterns. Applies stack-profile names React/Next.js; adopted marketplace (ECC) 2026-07-10; method conflicts resolve skill.